FBIS3-52957 "drnes006_j_94029" FBIS-NES-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen `Martyr al-Jihmi' Mourned JN0901091694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 0430 GMT 9 Jan 94 JN0901091694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] The preparatory committee of the [word indistinct] grouping has mourned the martyrdom of Shaykh 'Abd-al-Karim al-Jihmi, adviser to the prime ministry and member of the grouping's preparatory committee. While regretting this incident, which was carried out by vicious hands, the committee hopes that the competent security circles will quickly take the necessary measures, chase the culprits, and bring them to justice, so they can receive a just punishment. The committee also extends condolences to the martyr's family and kinsfolk. Funeral services for martyr al-Jihmi will be held at the martyrs' cemetery this morning, after prayers at the al-Shuhada' Mosque.
